Defendant Paris G Crossley in court with Attorney William Joseph Reddin.  Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Nicolla D.

AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FIFTEEN (15) years CONCURRENT to 14CF4053.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TEN (10) years with credit for 512 days time served.  Defendant shall serve FIVE (5) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

AS TO COUNT #3:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FIFTEEN (15) years CONCURRENT to 14CF4053.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TEN (10) years.  Defendant shall serve FIVE (5) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program 
The defendant IS eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program after SIX (6) years of incarceration.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon, he is not allowed to possess any body armour.
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - No contact with the victims, Jollene Y. and Michael S.;
 - Defendant to obtain his GED AND an Associate Degree;
 - Cooperate and participate with MENTAL HEALTH EVALUATION and any recommended treatment;
 - Take any and all medications prescribed to you;
 - Restitution in the amount of $500 to victim, Michael S.  This is to be paid BEFORE surcharges, fees and costs.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  If not paid, will result in an civil judgment;

Filed,
